oxidative stress. - Vitamin C contributes to normal collagen formation for the normal function of skin. - Zinc contributes to the maintenance of normal nails. - Zinc contributes to the normal function of the immune system.","validation":{"status":"failed","reasons":["unsafe_dose"],"summary":"One or more facts exceed safety limits.","checkedAt":"2026-05-21T10:12:53.982Z","matchableFactCount":4},"description":"Support radiant skin and collagen production with Hair Skin Nails+ (HSN+) by Swisse. Ideal for beauty-conscious consumers in Thailand.","priceAmount":650,"descriptionEn":"Daily supplement with biotin, zinc, nicotinamide, vitamin C sources and botanical extracts to support normal hair, skin and nail maintenance.","descriptionTh":"อาหารเสริมประจำวันที่มีไบโอติน สังกะสี นิโคตินาไมด์ แหล่งวิตามินซี และสารสกัดจากพืช เพื่อสนับสนุนการดูแลผม ผิว และเล็บให้ปกติ","extractedText":"Swisse HSN+ - Swisse Thailand Skip to content Products Back Products Beauty Eye Care Gummies Gut Health Immunity Joints, Bones, & Muscles Moisturisers Multivitamins Serums Skin Super Fruits & Herbs All Products Range Wellness Beauty Skincare About Back Our Story Ingredients Wellness Hub Sign in Search Cart (0) Cart empty Your cart is empty Continue shopping     svg]:w-full group-hover:text-uiGrey\"> Home / HSN+   Skip to product information Open media 1 in modal Open media 2 in modal Open media 3 in modal Swisse HSN+ SWISSE HSN+ is a quality formula containing hair, skin and nail vitamins e.g. Biotin, Niacin, Vitamin C, Zinc, Rosehips, Chamomile and green tea extract. Swisse committed to contributing positively to the needs of society and the planet, and we are the carbon neutral company. #Hair #Skin #Nails #HSN+ Sale price 650 ฿ Where to buy Buy at TikTok Buy at Shopee Buy at Lazada Buy at Line Benefits This unique formula with Zinc contributes to the maintenance of normal hair, skin, and nails. - Biotin contributes to the maintenance of normal hair.  - Biotin contributes to the maintenance of normal skin. - Niacin contributes to maintenance of normal mucous membrane of GI tract and normal skin.  - Vitamin C contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress.  - Vitamin C contributes to normal collagen formation for the normal function of skin. - Zinc contributes to the maintenance of normal nails. - Zinc contributes to the normal function of the immune system. Key Ingredients - Zinc 76.6 mg  - Nicotinamide 18 mg  - Calcium 42.4 mg  - Iron 16 mg, Biotin 30 mcg  - Rosehips extract 62.5 mg  - Chamomile powder extract 25 mg  - Green tea extract 8.3 mg Directions and Warnings DIRECTIONS: 1 tablet daily. Take during or immediately after a meal, or as directed by a healthcare professional. WARNINGS: Children, and pregnant women should not consume Should eat a variety of the five categories of food in appropriate proportions STORAGE: Store below 25C, in a cool, dry place. Do not use, if cap seal is broken. Reasons to love us We have been developing science-based formulas using premium ingredients sourced from around the world for over 50 years. We believe in natural ingredients being our hero ingredients. We also pursue the latest research findings to formulate our advanced product ranges and consistently strive to anticipate consumer demand. Backed by science Premium quality formula 50+ year heritage Certified B-Corp We are B-Corp Certified B Corps are for-profit companies that meet high standards of social and environmental performance, transparency, and accountability. Swisse is a brand of H&H Group, a certified B Corp. We feel honoured to be part of a global community using business as a force for good. Frequently Asked Questions What is the benefit of consuming Biotin daily? Biotin: As a member of the B vitamins group, Biotin is known to help strengthen soft, brittle nails and reduce breaking and splitting. What are the benefits of consuming foods rich in Niacin regularly? Foods containing niacin, also known as Vitamin B3, offer several health benefits. Supports the metabolism of carbohydrates, fats, and proteins. Helps regulate brain function and the nervous system. Maintains the health of the skin, tongue, and digestive tissues. Essential for the synthesis of sex hormones. Helps reduce cholesterol levels. Do we need to take vitamin supplements? The key is to ensure that we get a complete and balanced intake of nutrients each day. However, due to lifestyle limitations and dietary choices, we may not always receive the necessary nutrients in adequate amounts. In such cases, dietary supplements can be beneficial. Can Swisse products be taken alongside medication or medical treatments? Each individual has different nutritional and medicinal needs. If you are unsure whether Swisse products are suitable for you, it is best to consult a doctor. Please note that dietary supplements do not prevent, alter, or replace medical treatment or a well-balanced diet. What is the best time to take vitamins? Some supplements work best when taken with food, while others are more effective on an empty stomach. It is essential to follow the instructions on the label to maximize the benefits of each product. How long do dietary supplements last? In general, dietary supplements have a shelf life of approximately two years from the manufacturing date. Where does Swisse source its ingredients? We carefully select and source high-quality, premium-grade ingredients from around the world to ensure that only the best components go into our products. Where are Swisse products manufactured? Most of our products are manufactured in Australia. Please refer to the product packaging for the specific country of origin. The recommended dosage on the label applies to which age group? The recommended dosage is intended for individuals aged 18 and above. You may also like Swisse Biotin Forte with Vitamin C + Zinc Sale price 790 ฿ Swisse Ultivite Multivitamin with Folic Acid Sale price 650 ฿ Our Products Beauty Eye Care Gut Health Gummies Immunity J