 changes everything—support your daily wellness with Blackmores Vitamin C 500. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Immune System Health Common Colds & Flu Antioxidant for Free Radical Damage Collagen Formation No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits Maintains vitamin C levels in the body Supports immune system health. Reduces the severity and duration of common colds symptoms. Supports collagen formation. An antioxidant helping to reduce free radical damage to the body cells. Dosage Adults Take one tablet 1 to 2 times a day with meals or as prescribed by a health professional. Children under 18 years Only as prescribed by a health professional. Warnings Always read the label and follow directions for use. Adults only. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Suitable for use during pregnancy and breastfeeding. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Benefits Dosage Warnings Maintains vitamin C levels in the body Supports immune system health. Reduces the severity and duration of common colds symptoms. Supports collagen formation. An antioxidant helping to reduce free radical damage to the body cells. Adults Take one tablet 1 to 2 times a day with meals or as prescribed by a health professional. Children under 18 years Only as prescribed by a health professional. Always read the label and follow directions for use. Adults only. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Suitable for use during pregnancy and breastfeeding. If you have any pre-exist